{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PCAP header writing in macpdu2wireshark utility\n\n### Summary\nThe `write_pcap_header` function in the macpdu2wireshark tracing utility incorrectly used the same variable for both reserved fields in the PCAP file header. This could lead to corrupted packet capture files that fail to open in Wireshark, especially on big-endian systems or when compiler optimizations reuse the memory location.\n\nThe issue manifests as \"pcap: bogus savefile header\" errors when attempting to load the generated capture files. In some cases, the utility may appear to work but produce files with incorrect timestamp resolution or other header fields set to garbage values.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/macpdu2wireshark.c`: Separated the two reserved fields in the PCAP header into distinct variables (`reserved1` and `reserved2`) to prevent potential memory reuse issues. Added descriptive comments for each header field.\n"
}